Rendition tags logic

The rendition tag for position or esthetical look of the text is defined with the attribute @rend as rendition. Logic of rendition tags is following. The rendition is applied to the youngest child element inside nested elements. 
Example: 


<closer>
<salute rend="right"><lb facs="#facs_2_r1l38" n="N019"/><hi rend="italic">Dein Dich innigst liebender</hi>
<lb facs="#facs_2_l_19288" n="N021"/>vergante
<lb facs="#facs_2_r1l40" n="N020"/><hi rend="italic"><persName ref="persName.xml#fidelij">Fidelis</persName>.</hi></salute>
</closer>


All of the rendition tags are following:
-	right
-	left
-	center
-	italic
-	superscript
-	underlined

Element hi (highlight) with attribute italic is possible to applied to the single word. In case of antoher element denoting the word, hi elelemtn is outside of the element.

Example:
 <hi rend="italic"><persNameref="persName.xml#fidelij">Fidelis</persName>.</hi>



Annotation order

1.	Adding correspDesc
2.	Openers and closers 
3.	Defining people and places 
4.	Text specific features

